{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1450546139,"nonce":"Hb1GnmFcI2/CEPGmxsd0HeAj4us=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2NjAwNTc5Mg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/477#issuecomment-166005792"},"message":"\u003e Well, I'm just afraid of having to maintain a gcc build version for everything\n\nIf we would go down that way we would definitely be doing it wrong! \nThe advantage of having a compiler dependency shall not be that we won't encounter compiler specific issues anymore, but that we encounter them in the development/testing phase rather than in the production phase. If a package doesn't compile with the compiler present in iuc-tools, we know this upfront and the tool won't get into the toolshed until it's solved (preferably upstream). If something like that happens there must be a very good reason to add another compiler since C and C++ have standards.","files":null}]}